	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't think any comercial roms used that space.
<br />But I once hacked an FDS game to be mapper #0 with SRAM.  Just stuck a small loader on to copy the appropriate area to SRAM, then jump into the game.  (I also used simple RLE to make it a tad smaller so the loader would fit.)
<br />Some emulators refused to run it (mapper #0 isn't supposed to have sram), others ran it fine.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
